    LAMONOV_META_DESCRIPTION: "",
    LAMONOV_ABOUT:
      "<p>Dmitry Lamonov is a Russian contemporary artist specializing in typefaces. Typography is the theme of nearly all of his work. The emphasis in creativity is placed on working with Old Russian writing. In his works, he is based on the canonical structure of Old Russian letters, rethinking them in a new light and revealing them in different themes and forms. Dmitry Lamonov was born in 1987 in Leningrad, and has been living and working in Moscow since 2014. He is engaged in graphic design and contemporary art. Winner of international awards in the field of type design. The works were presented at various exhibitions in Russia and abroad. International Exhibition of Calligraphy in Moscow (2017), Calligraphic Biennale in Sharjah, UAE (2018).</p>",
    LAMONOV_WORK_1_TITLE: "Singularity",
    LAMONOV_WORK_1_TXT:
      '<p>A work from a series that combines calligraphy and illusion. The work presents the image of a black hole absorbing sunlight. <br>Text: "A red sun on white light heats the black earth."</p>',
    LAMONOV_WORK_2_TITLE: "Sweet Poster",
    LAMONOV_WORK_2_TXT:
      "<p>The work is a poster, the letters of which are associated with sweet. Looking at the picture, the hormone of happiness is activated in the body, similar to when we eat something sweet.</p>",
    LAMONOV_WORK_3_TITLE: "Five elements",
    LAMONOV_WORK_3_TXT:
      "<p>The work is an animation of five canvases combined into one. The works were created specifically for the 2018 Sharjah Calligraphy Biennial and are dedicated to the five elements - fire, water, earth, air and quintessence.</p>",
    LAMONOV_WORK_4_TITLE: "Saint Petersburg",
    LAMONOV_WORK_4_TXT:
      "<p>The work is dedicated to St. Petersburg. The strong opinion that St. Petersburg is the capital of the rains has been played up. The composition depicts a heavy layer of rain covering the city. In the rain streams erupting from each cloud, a different kind of rain is written. The Peter and Paul Fortress is depicted as a symbol of the city.</p>",
    LAMONOV_WORK_5_TITLE: "Cyrillic collection 2.0",
    LAMONOV_WORK_5_TXT:
      "<p>A series of experimental calligraphic works that explored the variety of type compositions that can be obtained using letters based on ancient Slavic writing.</p>",

